post_text: Our staff are back “together” today working virtually and in-person to learn and prepare for the coming school year. This morning we took a break from COVID-19 preparations to explore ways to be culturally responsive as we teach and connect with students and families.

post_text:
Forest Lake Area School Board tonight voted in favor of an administrative recommendation based on state guidance and COVID-19 case data, that Forest Lake Area Schools should begin the school year with in-person learning for students in grades K-6, including early childhood, and begin the school year in grades 7-12 with a hybrid learning model. A full distance learning option will also be provided for any student. District administration will also be prepared to adjust the opening plan if necessary according to case numbers and in consultation with the Minnesota Department of Health.

Families, stay tuned for further information as details become available.

post_text:
Important information about school meals as we transition into our summer food program:

Grab and go meal pickup, and meal deliveries to qualified families will continue through the end of our school year on Friday, June 5.

Beginning Monday, June 15th our summer meal program will begin offering grab and go breakfast and lunch meals for any child under the age of 18, and meal delivery for qualified families.

Those families who qualified for meal delivery during the school year are automatically qualified for meal delivery in the summer program. No additional application is needed.

Grab and go meal pickup will be offered from 10:00 a.m. to noon at the following locations:

Forest Lake Elementary
Lino Lakes Elementary
Wyoming Elementary
Forest Lake Area High School

Meals can be picked up from any location above, regardless of where your child attends school. Families do not need to call ahead before pickup. On Mondays, up to a week’s worth of meals may be picked up at one time.

post_text: Our facilities are opening up for youth sports practices and other activities. If you are organizing or participating in activities on school property, please make sure you're familiar with the guidelines so that we can all stay safe together.
shared_text:
Forest Lake Area Schools Community Education
May 29 at 3:19 PM ·

The safety and well-being of all students, families and staff will always be a top priority for Forest Lake Area Schools. Furthermore, the District fully recognizes the many physical, mental and emotional and social benefits that athletics and activities provide for youth and adult participants. Therefore, in accordance with the Minnesota Department of Health (MDH) Guidance for Social Distancing in Youth and Student Programs and Guidance for Social Distancing in Youth Sports, Forest Lake Area Schools facilities will begin a phased approach to allowing on-campus programming. Starting Monday, June 1, 2020, the use of outdoor facilities, along with a pilot program at the Sports Center and Community Pool, will be permitted in accordance with the guidelines listed below. Starting on Monday, June 8, the use of indoor facilities will be permitted, in accordance the District Facility Use guidelines. View the guidelines here: https://bit.ly/3eAcbhU

post_text: Today Governor Walz announced that distance learning will continue through our last day of school, June 5. Although we would have loved to have students back in their classrooms with us, we recognize these steps are important to protect the health of our students and our entire community. We know this announcement may prompt a lot of questions, so please check your email for additional information, or visit our website at www.flaschools.org/covid. We remain committed to supporting your child’s learning and staying connected in meaningful ways.

post_text: We are pleased to announce that Laurie Chelgren will be the new principal at Wyoming Elementary starting on July 1. Laurie is a highly regarded educator and leader with extensive classroom and student intervention teaching experience. She has been with Forest Lake Area Schools since 2002, most recently as the district’s Targeted Services and Tiered Intervention Coordinator. Congratulations to Laurie on this new role!

Forest Lake Area Schools is cancelling all after school and evening activities today, Friday, January 17. This includes all athletics, activities and extended day programming.

In addition, on both Friday and Saturday, all early childhood family education and preschool programs, Adult Basic Education, Community Education activities and community use of school facilities will be cancelled.

Childcare programs including SAC and Sonic will be open Friday until 6:00 PM for enrolled students at the regular site your child attends.

Students and families involved in Saturday high school activities should communicate with their coaches and advisors for up-to-date schedule information. Some events have been postponed or cancelled and others have been rescheduled for later in the day on Saturday.

post_text:
This morning at Forest Lake Area High School our school resource officer received a tip that one of our students had made threats about another student and that this person may possibly have a weapon. School staff immediately went into lockdown status while staff and police worked to locate the student in question.

School administrators and police were able to locate and apprehend the student and will continue to investigate the incident. There is no longer a threat to student or school safety and the lockdown has been lifted.

Student safety is always our first priority and we operate under an abundance of caution to help ensure that safety.

We are very thankful for the assistance of our school resource officer and Forest Lake Police Department, as well as the alert student who notified us of the possible threat.

post_text:
This week, community members had the opportunity to explore the hidden brain, where prior information and experiences are used subconsciously to make decisions every day.

“Every time we have a time constraint, our unconscious brain is going to take over...That’s great if the data you receive is correct, but what if it is not?”

This session was the first of three free learning sessions provided this fall from the Everyone Belongs project, a collaborative initiative of the Forest Lake Area School District, the YMCA Equity Innovation Center and area cities and townships. More information can be found at www.flaschools.org.

post_text:
Do you have little ones at home? Little Learners Play School is a great free opportunity for children ages 3-5. The program is offered as part of Forest Lake Area High School's Psychology of Childhood class and supervised by licensed teachers. The program is offered Tuesday-Friday in October from 11:40 a.m. to 2:10 p.m. (No Playschool October 17th-21st due to Fall Break).
Children are given the opportunity to develop small and large muscles, play with other children, explore new toys and surroundings, engage in songs and music, create art projects and learn concepts such as colors, numbers, and words during story time and learning activities.
You can enroll your child for 1, 2, 3, or all 4 days each week,
Register Online at https://www.flaschools.org/Page/3355

post_text: Introducing e-Learning days -- Beginning in the 2019-2020 school year, Forest Lake Area Schools students will have the ability to continue learning at home when school is cancelled due to weather. This change will eliminate the need to add back days to our school calendar in years when there is a frequent need for snow or cold weather cancellations. You can learn more about e-Learning days here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/142TOTnvg2HcV_EHeuk_2J-3pRwf3ghEANbVLX5Ilwpc/edit?usp=sharing

post_text: This has been an amazing year for our Forest Lake Ranger student athletes, coaches and fans. In 2018-2019, fourteen Ranger teams won SEC or section championships with eleven team appearances at state, including: Girls Cross Country, Boys Cross Country, Volleyball, Girls Basketball, Girls Nordic Skiing, Boys Nordic Skiing, Wrestling, Synchronized Swimming, Softball, Girls Lacrosse and Girls Golf. In individual competition, Ranger athletes represented our school at state in Gymnastics, Swim and Dive, Wrestling, Track and Field and Golf. In addition, FLAHS students made appearances at state tournaments in Speech, Debate and DECA. Congratulations Rangers! Job well done!

post_text: We are excited to announce that Forest Lake Area High School has been honored as a U.S. Department of Education Green Ribbon School. This honor recognizes the school for innovative efforts to reduce environmental impact and utility costs, improve health and wellness, and ensure effective sustainability education. FLAHS has a student Environmental Club that plans and implements several sustainability projects each year.

Due heavy snow and blizzard like conditions, Forest Lake Area Schools will be closed today, Thursday, April 11th. This includes early childhood family education and preschool programs. It also includes all after-school and evening athletics and activities, Adult Basic Education, Community Education activities and community use of school facilities.
Childcare programs including SAC, Sonic and Steps Ahead will be open from 6:00 AM - 6:00 PM for enrolled students at the following inclement weather sites: SAC and Sonic will be at Forest View Elementary, Wyoming Elementary, and Lino Lakes Elementary. Steps Ahead will be at the Central Learning Center and Lino Lakes Elementary.

post_text: Scandia Elementary 3rd graders have read their way to the Final Four in a statewide competition through myON that began with more than 200 elementary schools. Today, Governor Walz and myON staff took the time to congratulate the school for fostering a love of reading. Last night our school board approved a plan to make up missed school days and meet the state-required minimum. Under the approved plan, students will attend school on March 11 and April 22 (both previously scheduled as professional development and teacher work days). The plan will also require seniors to attend school with all other students on June 6 (previously scheduled as a day off for 12th grade students). An updated calendar is available at the link below.

We apologize for the inconvenience of changing our calendar mid-year. Thank you for your patience and understanding during this unusual winter.

Due to the forecast for heavy snow today, Forest Lake Area Schools will be closed today, Wednesday, February 20th. This includes early childhood family education and preschool programs. It also includes all after-school and evening athletics and activities, Adult Basic Education, Community Education activities and community use of school facilities.
Childcare programs including SAC, Sonic and Steps Ahead will be open from 6:00 AM - 6:00 PM for enrolled students at the following inclement weather sites: SAC and Sonic will be at Forest View Elementary, Wyoming Elementary, and Lino Lakes Elementary. Steps Ahead will be at and the Central Learning Center and Lino Lakes Elementary.

Due to the dangerously cold weather that is expected this week, Forest Lake Area Schools will be closed Tuesday, January 29th and Wednesday, January 30th. School district officials will monitor the National Weather Service forecasts and make a decision Wednesday afternoon about whether school will be open or closed on Thursday, January 31st.
This school closure includes early childhood family education and preschool programs. It also includes all after-school and evening athletics and activities, Adult Basic Education, community education activities and community use of school facilities.
Childcare programs including SAC, Sonic and Steps Ahead will be open from 6:00 AM - 6:00 PM for enrolled students at the following inclement weather sites: SAC and Sonic will be at Forest View Elementary, Wyoming Elementary, and Lino Lakes Elementary. Steps Ahead will be at and the Central Learning Center and Lino Lakes Elementary.
